<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="123" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="123">
<taxonomicName authorityName="K. D. Hyde, Nova Hedwigia 63 (1 - 2): 91" authorityYear="1996" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Amphisphaeriaceae" genus="Arecophila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Arecophila gulubiicola" order="Xylariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="gulubiicola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Arecophila gulubiicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has deeply immersed, subglobose to lenticular ascomata with a small or lacking clypeus, cylindrical, short-pedicellate asci with a wedge-shaped, conical, apical ring and ellipsoidal, brown ascospores with wall striations and surrounded by a mucilaginous sheath (
<bibRefCitation author="Hyde, KD" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" refId="B19" refString="Hyde, KD, 1996. Fungi from palms. XXIX. Arecophila gen. nov. (Amphisphaeriaceae, Ascomycota), with five new species and two new combinations. Nova Hedwigia 63(1/2): 81-100." title="Fungi from palms. XXIX. Arecophila gen. nov. (Amphisphaeriaceae, Ascomycota), with five new species and two new combinations. Nova Hedwigia 63 (1 / 2): 81 - 100." year="1996">Hyde 1996</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authority="Karun., C.H.Kuo &amp; K.D.Hyde, 2020" authorityName="Karun., C.H.Kuo &amp; K.D.Hyde" authorityYear="2020" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Amphisphaeriaceae" genus="Alishanica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Alishanica" order="Xylariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Alishanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been introduced as a monospecific genus with the type species 
<taxonomicName genus="Al." lsidName="Al. miscanthi" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="species" species="miscanthi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Al. miscanthi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Karun. et al. on dead sheaths of 
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Miscanthus" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Miscanthus sinensis" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sinensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Miscanthus sinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Miscanthus" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Poaceae</taxonomicName>
) from Taiwan (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5943/mycosphere/11/1/7" author="Hyde, KD" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" refId="B20" refString="Hyde, KD, Norphanphoun, C, Maharachchikumbura, SSN, Bhat, DJ, Jones, EBG, Bundhun, D, Chen, YJ, Bao, DF, Boonmee, S, Calabon, MS, 2020. Refined families of Sordariomycetes. Mycosphere 11(1): 305-1059. https://doi.org/10.5943/mycosphere/11/1/7" title="Refined families of Sordariomycetes. Mycosphere 11 (1): 305 - 1059." url="https://doi.org/10.5943/mycosphere/11/1/7" year="2020">Hyde et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
). We re-examined both 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. gulubiicola" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="species" species="gulubiicola">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">A. gulubiicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="Al." lsidName="Al. miscanthi" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="species" species="miscanthi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Al. miscanthi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
herbarium specimens and observed that they are congeneric. 
<taxonomicName authority="Karun., C.H.Kuo &amp; K.D.Hyde, 2020" authorityName="Li &amp; Zhang &amp; Lin &amp; Samarakoon &amp; Hyde &amp; Shen &amp; Liao &amp; Karunarathna &amp; Long &amp; Kang &amp; Kang" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Li &amp; Zhang &amp; Lin &amp; Samarakoon &amp; Hyde &amp; Shen &amp; Liao &amp; Karunarathna &amp; Long &amp; Kang &amp; Kang" baseAuthorityYear="2022" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Amphisphaeriaceae" genus="Alishanica" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Alishanica miscanthi" order="Xylariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="miscanthi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Alishanica miscanthi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has characters that immersed ascoma under a clypeus, unitunicate, cylindrical asci with a J+ apical ring and brown, 2-celled ascospores with longitudinal wall striations and a mucilaginous sheath which are consistent with the generic characteristics of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="K. D. Hyde, Nova Hedwigia 63 (1 - 2): 82" authorityYear="1996" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Amphisphaeriaceae" genus="Arecophila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Arecophila" order="Xylariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Arecophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The phylogeny of 
<taxonomicName genus="Al." lsidName="Al. miscanthi" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="species" species="miscanthi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Al. miscanthi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was mainly considered by the 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. bambusae" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" rank="species" species="bambusae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">A. bambusae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(HKUCC 4794) sequences (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5943/mycosphere/11/1/7" author="Hyde, KD" journalOrPublisher="Mycologia" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" refId="B20" refString="Hyde, KD, Norphanphoun, C, Maharachchikumbura, SSN, Bhat, DJ, Jones, EBG, Bundhun, D, Chen, YJ, Bao, DF, Boonmee, S, Calabon, MS, 2020. Refined families of Sordariomycetes. Mycosphere 11(1): 305-1059. https://doi.org/10.5943/mycosphere/11/1/7" title="Refined families of Sordariomycetes. Mycosphere 11 (1): 305 - 1059." url="https://doi.org/10.5943/mycosphere/11/1/7" year="2020">Hyde et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
). However, HKUCC 4794 is not the type material of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="K. D. Hyde, Nova Hedwigia 63 (1 - 2): 82" authorityYear="1996" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Amphisphaeriaceae" genus="Arecophila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Arecophila" order="Xylariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Arecophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and cannot be used to represent 
<taxonomicName authorityName="K. D. Hyde, Nova Hedwigia 63 (1 - 2): 82" authorityYear="1996" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Amphisphaeriaceae" genus="Arecophila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Arecophila" order="Xylariales" pageId="0" pageNumber="123" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="123">Arecophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In our phylogeny, HKUCC 4794 forms a distinct clade (Fig. 
